1:1 COMMENT "# io_stat_mkdirp.z -- create a nested directory tree, then stat it."
1:68 EOL "\n"
2:1 COMMENT "#"
2:2 EOL "\n"
3:1 COMMENT "# `io.mkdirp` walks the path creating each missing component with"
3:66 EOL "\n"
4:1 COMMENT "# mode 0755 (like `mkdir -p`). `io.stat` reports metadata through"
4:66 EOL "\n"
5:1 COMMENT "# `filestat`: a `filekind` discriminant (file / dir / symlink /"
5:64 EOL "\n"
6:1 COMMENT "# other) and a byte `size`. `stat` follows symlinks and reports the"
6:68 EOL "\n"
7:1 COMMENT "# target; use `io.lstat` to inspect the link itself. A directory's"
7:67 EOL "\n"
8:1 COMMENT "# stat size is filesystem-dependent, so only a written file's size"
8:67 EOL "\n"
9:1 COMMENT "# (its byte count) is printed."
9:31 EOL "\n"
10:1 COMMENT "#"
10:2 EOL "\n"
11:1 COMMENT "# Inside `case ok then { ... }` the subject `s` is narrowed to"
11:63 EOL "\n"
12:1 COMMENT "# filestat, so field access reads directly: `s.size`, `s.kind`."
12:64 EOL "\n"
13:1 EOL "\n"
